p: In a sensitivity analysis that assumes âˆ¼20 times more undetected importations, we found that the estimated risks decreased further ( S1 Fig). We also varied the number of detected autochthonous cases in November: as they decrease from one to zero, the estimated risks decrease considerably; as they increase to five, estimated risks increase, with 83 counties becoming at risk for a local outbreak ( S1 Fig). However expected transmission risk for these counties is still well below 1, ranging from 0.3-0.6.
